body:
A duplicate of #1431 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/287898): - shellharden - shfmt To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. [restyled]: https://restyled.io [documentation]: https://github.com/restyled-io/restyled.io/wiki/Disabling-Restyled --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/1626)

commit.message: make ToxAV independent of toxcore internals.
format with astyle and run apidsl.

turn "switch" into "if".
fix some tokstyle errors.

fix more toktok style errors.
put toxav_get_av_mono_time in toxav_hacks.h.
put more function defs into toxav_hacks.h.

Merge the whole toxav library into one.

Bye bye modularity.
fix logger.c and logger.h and remove debug stuff.
